# === Build System Artifacts ===
# I am ignoring the entire build directory because these files are platform-specific.
# I want my CI/CD and my teammates to generate their own binaries from scratch.
build/
bin/
lib/

# === C++ Tooling & Compilation ===
# I am blocking object files and static/shared libraries. 
# I only want to track source code, not the heavy results of compilation.
*.o
*.obj
*.a
*.la
*.lo
*.so
*.so.*
*.dylib
*.exe
*.out

# I am ignoring this file because it contains absolute paths from my local machine.
# I need CMake to regenerate this inside the Dev Container or the CI/CD environment.
compile_commands.json

# === IDE & Editor Specifics ===
# I am ignoring the general VS Code folder to keep my personal UI preferences local.
.vscode/*

# I am making an exception for these two files. 
# I want to share my recommended extensions and debug configurations with the team.
!.vscode/extensions.json
!.vscode/launch.json

# I am blocking Vim and JetBrains (CLion) temporary files to keep the repo clean.
*.swp
*.swo
.idea/
cmake-build-*/

# === System & OS Junk ===
# I am ignoring these hidden OS files that add zero value to the code logic.
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db

# === Docker & Environment ===
# I am blocking any temporary files generated by the Dev Container extension.
.devcontainer/internal/
.env